columns.name: MS_ID
columns.dc:description: Manuscript identifier, or identifier of a partial manuscript when suffixed by a letter

columns.name: item
columns.dc:description: item is a unique number for each constituent piece of writing in a given manuscript. Where a piece of writing is in multiple languages, each language element in the piece is assigned a distinct item number.

columns.name: title
columns.dc:description: title is the title or first few words of a work contained in a given manuscript.

columns.name: language
columns.dc:description: language is the language used in a given item. Expected values are French, Latin, English and Other.

columns.name: start_folio
columns.dc:description: start_folio is the folio number on which the beginning of a given item can be found. Numbers are expected.

columns.name: start_side
columns.dc:description: start_side is the side of the folio on which the beginning of a given item can be found. Expected values are r (recto: usually the right hand page of an open book) and v (verso: usually the left hand page of an open book).

columns.name: end_folio
columns.dc:description: end_folio is the folio number on which the end of a given item can be found. Numbers are expected.

columns.name: end_side
columns.dc:description: end_side is the side of the folio on which the end of a given item can be found. Expected values are r (recto: usually the right hand page of an open book) and v (verso: usually the left hand page of an open book).

columns.name: ordinal_start
columns.dc:description: Start page of a text, counting from 1 when start_folio is a Arabic numeral and starting from 100001 when start_side is a Roman numeral.

columns.name: ordinal_end
columns.dc:description: End page of a text, counting from 1 when end_folio is a Arabic numeral and starting from 100001 when end_side is a Roman numeral.

columns.name: total_sides
columns.dc:description: Total number of pages that this text counts for.
